# Built by dot-update.d/ollama as the `offload` model - `ollama run offload`
# locally, or http://llm.home from any other machine on the LAN.
#
# Same role as tiny_lappy's Modelfile.offload (low-stakes tasks offloaded
# from Claude to save cost) but tuned for what this box actually has:
# Ryzen 5 5500 (6c/12t) and an 8GB card, vs. the laptop's CPU-only 2c/4t.
# Built FROM the 7b model (better reasoning/coding than the 3b one also
# pulled here) with a bigger num_ctx - there's headroom for it once a
# request is running, and OLLAMA_KEEP_ALIVE (set in dot-update.d/ollama's
# systemd drop-in) releases that headroom back to the house between calls.
# This is the one worth waiting on; tiny_lappy's is the instant-but-dumber
# fallback for when htpc/the LAN isn't reachable.
#
# Tuned for fast, low-stakes tasks handed down from Claude to save cost:
# formatting, summarizing, extracting data, boilerplate, straightforward
# lookups. Not for code review or anything reasoning-heavy - that stays
# with Claude.
#
# Copy this file (Modelfile.<name>) and change FROM / PARAMETER / SYSTEM to
# build other tuned variants, then:
#   ollama create <name> -f ollama/Modelfile.<name>
# No re-download - relayering an already-pulled base is instant.
#
# Full parameter reference: https://github.com/ollama/ollama/blob/main/docs/modelfile.md

FROM qwen2.5:7b

PARAMETER temperature 0.3
PARAMETER top_p 0.9
PARAMETER num_ctx 8192
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.1

SYSTEM """
You are a fast local assistant handling small, well-defined tasks offloaded
from a larger assistant to save cost - formatting, summarizing, extracting
data, boilerplate generation, straightforward lookups. Answer directly and
concisely. If a task needs deep reasoning, broad context, or a judgment call
you're not confident in, say so plainly instead of guessing.
"""
